text: Nicholas Comoroto (born April 22, 1991) is an American professional wrestler. He currently wrestles for All Elite Wrestling (AEW) and their sister promotion Ring of Honor (ROH). Comoroto has also made appearances in EVOLVE, WWE, and New Japan Pro-Wrestling (NJPW), Impact Wrestling, and WWE. In WWE, he was known by the ring name Nick Ogarelli. ==Career== ===All Elite Wrestling / Ring of Honor === On the October 13, 2020 episode of Dark, Comoroto made his AEW debut in a loss to Darby Allin. On the January 26, 2021 episode of Dark, Comoroto earned his first victory in AEW when he teamed with Dustin Rhodes and QT Marshall to defeat Ryan Nemeth, Shawn Dean and Vary Morales. At Double or Nothing, Comoroto entered the Casino Battle Royal but the match was won by Jungle Boy. On May 30, 2024 episode of ROH on HonorClub, Comoroto and Jacoby Watts challenged The Undisputed Kingdom (Matt Taven and Mike Bennett) for their ROH World Tag Team Championships in a proving ground match but were unsuccessful in winning the championships. == References == ==Other websites== * Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:All Elite Wrestling people Category:American professional wrestlers Category:Former WWE wrestlers Category:Sportspeople from New Jersey
